    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-27T23:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-27T23:41:00-05:00" n="1546"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1546">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/73.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Canova</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-27T22:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring your July 22, 3 p.m., shall I go to Zacatecas? General Natera returns
                    from Tampico to-morrow night and I can make trip with him. Nothing definite can
                    be accomplished at Zacatecas until he returns. Please advise me here. Carranza
                    has already recommended me highly to Natera. Fabela informs me by wire from
                    Tampico that Sanchez de la Vega, acting Governor of Zacatecas, has been
                    instructed to assist me in every possible manner.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
